revious articles, our focus here is\nagain on low regularity data and on the interaction between different types of\nboundary conditions. While our work here serves primarily to extend the\nsolution theory for the compact with boundary case, we also develop several\ntechnical tools that have potential for use with the asymptotically Euclidean\ncase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Oct 2013 23:06:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 2013 01:18:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-22"}
