{"id":"1310.2465","submitter":"Juliana Xavier","authors":"Juan Alonso, Nancy Guelman and Juliana Xavier","title":"Actions of solvable Baumslag-Solitar groups on surfaces with\n  (pseudo-)Anosov elements","comments":"new version with improvements","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $BS(1,n)= <a,b : a b a ^{-1} = b ^n>$ be the solvable Baumslag-Solitar\ngroup, where $n \\geq 2$. We study representations of $BS(1, n)$ by\nhomeomorphisms of closed surfaces with (pseudo-)Anosov elements. That is, we\nconsider a closed surface $S$, and homeomorphisms $f, h: S \\to S$ such that $h\nf h^{-1} = f^n$, for some $ n\\geq 2$. It is known that $f$ (or some power of\n$f$) must be homotopic to the identity. Suppose that $h$ is pseudo-Anosov with\nstretch factor $\\lambda >1$. We show that $<f,h>$ is not a faithful\nrepresentation of $BS(1, n)$ if $\\lambda > n$. Moreover, we show that there are\nno faithful representations of $BS(1, n)$ by torus homeomorphisms with $h$ an\nAnosov map and $f$ area preserving (regardless of the value of $\\lambda$).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Oct 2013 13:19:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Oct 2013 13:07:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 26 May 2014 18:40:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-05-27"}
